		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="en">The raw brine is directly sourced from underground and sent to the plant, where the pretreatment stage is the first step. The raw brine is heated in this section, and its pH is fixed for an optimized extraction. The pretreated brine then follows the DLE process, generating a stream about ten times more concentrated in lithium. At the next stage of the process, more reagents are required to modify the process conditions and remove impurities. Sodium hydroxide, hydrochloric acid, polymer, and other reagents are crucial for precipitating and removing the sludge from the brine, like chloride removal (Rahmani et al., 2019). In the lithium concentration section, the concentration in the brine increases about 15 times. Any surplus water from this process is then directed to the freshwater generation unit. The process involves using antiscalant, sodium hydroxide, and other reagents to adjust the pH and chloride levels of the brine. Additionally, this process relies on energy consumption in the form of electricity to concentrate the brine through pressure. The final stage of producing lithium carbonate in this plant is converting the dissolved lithium to solid lithium carbonate through sodium carbonate. The final stage, in which freshwater is generated, focuses on recovering water from the brines for use as freshwater in the plant by adding various additives to balance the pH and remove impurities</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="zh">原盐水直接取自地下，送至工厂，预处理阶段是第一步。在这一阶段，原盐水会被加热，其 pH 值也会被固定，以优化萃取效果。经过预处理的盐水随后进入 DLE 流程，产生的锂流浓度约为原来的十倍。在工艺的下一阶段，需要更多试剂来改变工艺条件和去除杂质。氢氧化钠、盐酸、聚合物和其他试剂对于沉淀和去除盐水中的污泥（如去除氯化物）至关重要（Rahmani 等人，2019 年）。在锂浓缩段，盐水的浓度增加了约 15 倍。此过程中多余的水将被导入淡水生成装置。该过程需要使用防垢剂、氢氧化钠和其他试剂来调节盐水的 pH 值和氯化物含量。此外，该工艺还需要消耗电力，通过压力浓缩盐水。该工厂生产碳酸锂的最后阶段是通过碳酸钠将溶解的锂转化为固体碳酸锂。产生淡水的最后阶段，主要是从盐水中回收水，通过添加各种添加剂来平衡 pH 值和去除杂质，以用作工厂的淡水。</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">Battery-grade lithium carbonate produced through direct lithium extraction in Clinton Valley, Nevada, USA, is primarily used in lithium-ion batteries, which are used in a wide range of portable electronic devices, electric vehicles and grid energy storage solutions.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">通过美国内华达州克林顿谷直接锂提取技术生产的电池级碳酸锂主要用于锂离子电池，这类电池广泛应用于便携式电子设备、电动汽车和电网储能解决方案中。</technologicalApplicability>
